Kwame Brown - Points

Kwame Brown scores a career high 30 points (2004)

On March 17, 2004, Kwame Brown set his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 30 points in Washington's home win against Sacramento, 114-108. He also had 19 rebounds, 3 assists, 2 steals. He shot 12/16 from two, shooting at 75.0% from the field. He also shot 6/7 from the free-throw line.

Kwame Brown - Rebounds

Kwame Brown grabs a career high 19 rebounds (2004)

On March 17, 2004, Kwame Brown set his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 19 rebounds in Washington's home win against Sacramento, 114-108. He also had 30 points, 3 assists, 2 steals.

Kwame Brown - Assists

Kwame Brown gives a career high 7 assists (2006)

On December 08, 2006, Kwame Brown set his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 7 assists in LA Lakers's home win against Atlanta, 106-95. He also had 13 points, 7 rebounds and 1 block.

Kwame Brown - Steals

Kwame Brown has a career high 5 steals (2009)

On March 15, 2009, Kwame Brown set his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 5 steals in Detroit's home loss against Memphis, 84-89. He also had 6 points, 13 rebounds.

Kwame Brown - Blocks

Kwame Brown blocks a career high 6 shots (2002)

On October 31, 2002, Kwame Brown set his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 6 blocks in Washington's home win against Boston, 114-69. He also had 20 points, 6 rebounds and 1 assist.

Kwame Brown - Efficiency

Kwame Brown records a career high 48 efficiency rating (2004)

On March 17, 2004, Kwame Brown set his career high in efficiency in a NBA game. That day he accomplished 48 efficiency in Washington's home win against Sacramento, 114-108. He also had 30 points, 19 rebounds and 3 assists.
